Ever feel like your zombie server could use a little change up?  This map is a visual breath of fresh air.  Plenty of camping spots all over the map to explore and try out.  No impenetrable spots (like 1 way tunnels with couches nearby), but plenty of difficult to attack spots.  It's a good sized map, but not too large or elongated, which tends to separate the action.  It's pretty open, so you should have a good amount of zombies in your view to shoot at and keep from getting bored.

*** BETA VERSION 2 ***

Complete rework, and improvements to some of the spots thanks to Robin.  This newer version is much better, almost every spot has been reworked to balance it out.  Please send constructive suggestions for improvements, I will work everything into Beta 3.

After a few month's work the map is finally complete! The map has gone through several private alpha and beta tests to make sure there are no gameplay or graphical errors. The map was tested on two servers:

72.249.10.10:27015
80.190.78.54:27015

Both are great servers, so be sure to check them out.

The story:

"The map will be based in an overgrown, ancient factory. Think of the soft wind rustling through the cracks and holes of a by gone time. With the eerie silence that completely surrounds you, a chill runs down your spine. What happened here to make the inhabitance leave in such a hurry? What would make them abandon this place completely?"

The map is made for servers with about 25-32 slots. The map is still playable with less people, but since the map is large, the action will be less centralized. I will release a smaller version in a week's time.

Features:
-High FPS (80-100).
-Graphics that show ZM map don't have to full bright and ugly, but has teh gameplay that makes ZM fun.
-Barricading and camping.
-Throughly tested for game-breaking bugs
-HDR
-Large, detailed environment that will draw you into the game.

Credits:

-Caid for two of the smaller areas for me to detail. (Good job on them, but work on keeping it on grid :P).
-Games and Error.ocx;s servers for the private testing.
-Der.Zoomer for finding bugs that I didn't even know could exist.
-And everybody else who encouraged me!

Thanks, and happy hunting!

This is my redux of the map zm_deep_thought. I created this map because I was frustrated with the many deficencies of the original zm_deep_thought. The original map was too small, the brushwork wasn't that great and the lighting was inconsistent and irritating. Also bar the two really cheap spots, there were only 3-4 good places for humans to hold up.

Unlike other remakes of zm_deep_thought that just add on more to the existing problematic level, my version is a from scratch, ground up remake. No existing geometry was used from the old map, so I was free to make the new level how I wanted without the constraints of the old level to hamper the design.

One of the things I spent more time than I probably should have was the lighting. The old level had really ugly blotchy lighting that was really inconsistent. Blues with sickly yellows and bright reds really makes for something nasty. In the new map, I used mostly warmer tones of light on the outer areas and cooler tones on the inner areas of the level to divide the indoor and outdoor aspects of the map.

I hope everyone can enjoy the visual aspects of the map as well as the gameplay. Long hours were spent by myself debugging weird crashing issues, texture issues and more model issues you can shake a stick at.
